org.nustaq.offheap.structs.structtypes

Class StructArray<E extends FSTStruct>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nustaq.offheap.structs.FSTStruct
      • org.nustaq.offheap.structs.structtypes.StructArray<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class StructArray<E extends FSTStruct>
extends FSTStruct
    An array whose elements are stored 'off heap'. Note that in current version (and documentation below) 'off-heap' means that objects are stored in flat byte arrays. Those byte arrays are actually allocated on the regular java heap. This is not exactly the definition of "off-heap" as this term usually means that raw 'Unsafe' memory is allocated. However using some tweaks it might be possible to back FSTStructs by real off-heap in a furture version if the need arises.

    Serialized Form

      • StructArray

        public StructArray(int size,
                   E template)
        initializes with a template. When off heaped, all elements are filled with a copy of that template. Warning: if this is used, this class behaves different off-heap compared to on-heap. On Heap the template element is ignored.
